Detailed Description

The Power Management IC (PMIC) tps65917 specific API definition.

The APIs defined here are to control the voltage of the PMIC rails and to query the status.

#define PMHAL_TPS65917_SLAVE_ADDR_COUNT   (5U)

Slave Address:

The TPS65917 PMIC uses the standard 7-bit slave I2C address to access the register address space. This PMIC has 5 internal pages each of 256 bytes. The register address is 8-bits and can address one page. Multiple pages are addressed using different slave addresses. The table below gives the slave address for the register pages as programmed in the TDA2xx device EVMs.

Function Documentation

void PMHALTps65917ConfigureRegulatorMap ( pmhalTps65917RegulatorMapPtr_t  regulatorMap)

The PMIC regulator output to the device input mapping can be different on different boards. This API can be used to provide a different mapping to the PMIC driver if the mapping does not

match the default. Example table is shown below:

| Device voltage Rail | Ptr to Regulator |

| PMHAL_PRCM_PMIC_REGULATOR_MPU | PMHAL_TPS65917_REGULATOR_SMPS1 | | PMHAL_PRCM_PMIC_REGULATOR_CORE | PMHAL_TPS65917_REGULATOR_SMPS2 | | .... | | index (Refer | For index of the | | pmhalPrcmPmicRegulatorId_t) | gPmhalTps65917Regulator | | | refer |

| | pmhalTps65917RegulatorId_t |

This table when translated to code is as below: pmhalTps65917RegulatorMap_t regulatorMap[ PMHAL_PRCM_PMIC_REGULATOR_COUNT] = { { &gPmhalTps65917Regulator[PMHAL_TPS65917_REGULATOR_SMPS1], I2C_INSTANCE, PMIC_I2C_SLAVE_ADDRESS }, { &gPmhalTps65917Regulator[PMHAL_TPS65917_REGULATOR_SMPS2], I2C_INSTANCE, PMIC_I2C_SLAVE_ADDRESS }, ...... };.

Parameters
regulatorMapPointer to the array of pointers which gives the mapping. The array is defined as above.
Returns
None
